## Production data flow

Students submit their local `lesson4-ready-for-lesson5-v1` package into a long-lived class question pool.

Do not import Lesson4 cloud DB as production logic.

## Debug data flow

Before live UI work, build fixture inspection and seeding from:

```text
backend/runtime/fixtures/module4/lesson5/cloud_lesson4_question_bank/
backend/runtime/fixtures/module4/lesson5/student_portfolio_json/
```

Compare both sources and generate normalized fixture submissions. Do not commit raw real student data.

## Required architecture

```text
Student lesson: src/modules/module-4-ai-info-detective/lessons/lesson-5/
Teacher console: src/teacher-console/
Backend: backend/app/modules/module4/lesson5/
```

## Required database split

```text
auth_and_classes.sql
question_bank.sql
lesson5_runtime.sql
```

## Hard rules

- Class pool starts empty.
- First V2 submission creates first pool item/version.
- Teacher selects class before creating session.
- Sessions can be normal/makeup/test.
- Locking a session freezes current V2 versions.
- Assignments use frozen session pool only.
- Assignments exclude self-authored items.
- Answer and rating are separate steps.
- Stats are session-scoped.
- V3 is stored as ready_for_lesson6.
- Stage snapshot HTML is generated locally.
- Demo role is read-only and backend-enforced.
- No WebSocket in v0.1.
- No Q-score frequency adjustment in v0.1.

## Build order

1. SQL and fixture seed.
2. Auth and class permissions.
3. V2 class pool.
4. Teacher session control.
5. Student attach and assignments.
6. Answer/rating.
7. Stats/report.
8. V3 and local snapshot.
